<HEADLINE> Party, Government Officials Attend Art Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and other Party and Government officials tonight attended an art
performance in Beijing to greet the Lunar New Year, or the Spring
Festival.
</P>
<P>
Present at the show were Li Peng, Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People Congress, Premier Zhu Rongji, Li
Ruihuan, Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People'
s Political Consultative Conference, and Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing
and Li Lanqing, who are all members of the Standing Committee of
the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Also present included Chi Haotian, Zhang Wannian, Luo Gan, Jia
Qinglin, Wen Jiabao, and Zeng Qinghong.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the party was China's great achievements in reform,
opening-up and socialist modernization, the unity between the army
and the people, and the new look of the armed forces under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory on army building at the new era
and of Jiang's important expositions on army building.
</P>
<P>
All the programs of the party were created and played by
amateur performers of the army.  
</P>
</TEXT>
