<HEADLINE> One Killed, Over 100 Injured in Hartal in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and over
100 people were injured on Thursday in the last day of the
opposition-sponsored 60-hour hartal (general strike) across
Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The person was killed in northwest Chittagong district in
clashes between pro- and anti-hartal activists, and a policeman,
who received bomb injuries during hartal hours on Tuesday, died in
a hospital here on Thursday, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city, five to 10 people were injured during a
clash between activists of the Jamaat-e-Islami and the ruling
Bangladesh Awami League, and about 90 people were arrested across
the country during the shutdown.
</P>
<P>
Despite sporadic clashes, life was fairly normal in Dhaka, with
large numbers of rickshaws and some buses plying on the streets.
Banks, financial institutions and most private offices operated
normally, but educational institutions still remained closed.
</P>
<P>
The opposition alliance, comprising the major opposition
--Bangladesh Nationalist Party, the Jatiya Party, the
Jamaat-e-Islami and others, called the countrywide hartal to press
home their four-point demand, including replacement of the chief
election commissioner, for joining the country's municipal
elections scheduled to be held later this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
