<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus' Trade Deficit up in 11 Months of 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' trade deficit
increased in the first eleven months of 1998 by 6.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to a report released Thursday by Cyprus' official
Department of Statistics and Research, total exports in the first
eleven months of 1998 decreased by 13.3 percent to 514.2 million
Cyprus pounds (1.028 billion U.S. dollars) from the same period in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, total imports decreased by 0.3 percent to 1.738
billion pounds (3.476 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
As a result, trade deficit in the January-November period
reached 1.224 billion pounds (2.448 billion dollars), which
represents an increase of 6.5 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Europe Union countries absorbed 52.9 percent of Cyprus'
exports, compared to 49.5 percent in the corresponding period of
1997.
</P>
<P>
As for the island's imports, the EU share was 54.6 percent,
compared to 47.6 percent in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
