<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Confident About Economy in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Bank of Zambia Governor Gacob
Mwanza said Thursday the Zambian economy is likely to register
positive growth this year as the privatization of the mines is
finalized.
</P>
<P>
Mwanza said 1999 would be a year of various economic activities
 following the resumption of balance of payment support by
Zambia's cooperating partners.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking on behalf of Finance Minister Edith Nawakwi at
the launching of the Zambia Investment Grouping Insurance Company
(ZIGI) in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
The launching of the ZIGI has come at the right time and that
it shows that local investors have confidence in the economy, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He observed that this would send positive signals to supplement
local efforts in promoting economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Mwanza also noted that the new insurance company would create
employment for the local people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
