<HEADLINE> UK Companies Unveil Smart Refrigerator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Two British companies have
produced a smart refrigerator that writes shopping lists and even
tells when you are out of milk, The Daily Telegraph newspaper said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The freezer, developed by the computer company ICL and the
electronics manufacturer Electrolux, can remember what food is
inside to advise people when stores are running low.
</P>
<P>
It uses a barcode scanner to register food going in and out,
and can also be connected to the Internet to order and pay for
food.
</P>
<P>
David Cox, of ICL, predicted that in the future the
supermarkets may lease the smart refrigerators to their customers
so that they know their customers' eating habits.
</P>
<P>
Three prototypes have been built by the two companies, and the
next stage is to add voice recognition function to the smart
refrigerator, The Daily Telegraph said.  
</P>
