<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Labor Department
said Thursday the number of first-time claims for unemployment benefits
dropped by 13,000 last week to a seasonally adjusted 281,000, the
lowest level since July 1997.
</P>
