<HEADLINE> LIFFE To Accelerate It's New Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) announced Thursday
it will launch its international bond futures contracts onto its
new electronic trading platform, LIFFE ConnectTM, on 10 May 1999.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Exchange announced that its UK stock index
products will transfer from the trading floor to the LIFFE
ConnectTM system on 10 May, and that it will add its pan-European
stock index products on 25 May.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE ConnetTM is a new generation electronic trading platform
which has been designed and developed in-house by the LIFFE at a
cost of 10.5 million pounds for equities and 25 million pounds for
futures.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, trading in equity options, the
first products to be transferred from the trading floor to LIFFE
ConnectTM, has increased by 37 percent since the transfer.
</P>
<P>
Since the move to ConnectTM on 30 November they have traded an
average daily volume of 18,361 contracts compared to an average
daily volume of 13,419 contracts, over the same time period in
1998.
</P>
<P>
Hugh Freedberg, LIFFE's Chief Executive said: "The acceleration
of the roll-out program is testimony to the growing confidence
among our customers in our new electronic trading platform."
</P>
<P>
"Our partnership with 16 independent software vendors offers
our customers the widest choice anywhere of front end software
packages," he added. 
</P>
