said earlier in Washington that his government is perturber and
worried about U.S. policy on Angola. He said U.S. has treated
UNITA Chairman Jonas Savimbi, a criminal of Angola's civil war, on
the equal footing with the legitimate government, which is
unacceptable to the Angolan government.
</P>
<P>
Under Schneidman's itinerary in Angola, he will held talks with
Defense Minister Kundi Paihama and leader of the breakaway group,
UNITA Renovation Committee, Eugenio Manuvakula, in addition to
ministers of petroleum, planning and foreign affairs. 
