<HEADLINE> Annan Briefs Security Council on African, Balkan Conflicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Thursday morning briefed the Security Council on
conflicts in Africa and the Serbian Province of Kosovo, Fred
Eckhard, U.N. spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief, in his briefing postponed due to his earlier
presence at the funeral of late King Hussein in Jordan, touched on
the conflicts in Sierra Leone, Angola, Congo (K) and the Central
African Republic, Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to speak to the press here soon after he
finished his briefing at a closed-door Security Council session,
U.N. Spokesman's Office announced. 
</P>
