<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 26 Injured in Accidents in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and 26
others injured on Thursday in two separate traffic accidents in
southern Egypt, the Middle East News Agency here reported.
</P>
<P>
In the west area of Asyut Governorate, about 300 kilometers
south of Cairo, five vehicles ran into each other due to a dense
fog, killing eight people and wounding 12, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
In another accident, two tourist buses collided on the Red Sea
coastal road, killing a German tourist and injuring 14 others, a
statement issued by the Egyptian Interior Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place when one tourist bus driving from Qena,
450 kilometers south of the capital, to Hurghada, 400 southeast of
Cairo, overtook another car but suddenly swerved to the opposite
lane and collided with the other tourist bus.
</P>
<P>
The injured, six of them in serious condition, have been taken
to hospitals for treatment, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt as vehicles are often
driven at high speed and drivers impatient. In the past three
weeks, 42 people were killed and 61 others wounded in road
accidents. 
</P>
