<HEADLINE> U.S. Jet Bombs Iraqi Site in Third Day of Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. F-15E bombed an
Iraqi anti-aircraft artillery site on Friday in response to Iraqi
fire in the northern no-fly zone, a U.S. military official said.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at about 1:30 p.m. Iraqi time (0830 GMT)
near the city of Mosul.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. fighter jet dropped one GBU-12 precision-guided bomb
on the site, said air force Captain Mike Blass, spokesman for the
U.S. European Command in Stuttgart, Germany, which oversees the
northern zone.
</P>
<P>
He said there was no damage to U.S. aircraft and damage to the
Iraqi site was being assessed.
</P>
<P>
It was the third consecutive day that U.S. warplanes bombed
Iraqi air defense sites.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iraqi News Agency, one U.S. plane "fired a
missile at random on a civilian installation ... which led to the
martyrdom of one person and the wounding of another". 
</P>
</TEXT>
