<HEADLINE> Bank in Nicosia Robbed, Police Manhunt Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot police on Friday
launched a manhunt for two young armed robbers, who raided a
branch of Cyprus Bank in central Nicosia, in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Police said the two robbers, wearing stockings and motor
helmets and wielding pistols, rushed into the bank at 9:25 local
time (0725 GMT) and got away with some 50-60 thousand Cypriot
pounds (95-114 thousand U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to witnesses, the two youths, about 25-30 years old,
took the money and escaped on a red and white dirt bike with false
plates. One of them fired a shot in the air.
</P>
<P>
Police cordoned off the area and set up roadblocks. A
helicopter was being use in the police manhunt. 
</P>
