<HEADLINE> Re-exports Take Larger Share of HK's External Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua)-- Hong Kong's re-exports
accounted for 86 percent of the value of total exports and 41.7
percent of the total value of external trade of Hong Kong in 1998.
</P>
<P>
And they were slightly higher than the corresponding shares of
85.5 percent and 40.5 percent in 1997, according to the figures
released by the Census and Statistics Department here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese mainland remained the largest partner for Hong Kong'
s re-export trade. As a source, re-exports originating from the
mainland accounted for 59.6 percent of the value of re-exports of
Hong Kong in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Other main origins of Hong Kong's re-exports in 1998 included
Japan (accounting for 10.7 percent), Taiwan region (6.2 percent),
the United States (4.7 percent) and the Republic of Korea (3.4
percent). 
</P>
