<HEADLINE> EU Approves Opening Banking Joint Venture in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
here on Friday that it had approved the establishment of a joint
venture in the Greek banking sector after a month-long
investigation.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU)'s executive body concluded that the
operation between Inchcape Holdings Hellas and EFG Eurobank does
not raise any competition concerns in the Greek market for
consumer financing services.
</P>
<P>
Although under a legal obligation to provide the full spectrum
of banking services, the joint venture, to be called Autofin S.A.,
is intended to be active mainly in the provision of consumer
financing for the purchase of new and used cars, motorcycles and
leisure boats, the commission noted.
</P>
<P>
The operation is not likely to raise serious doubts about its
compatibility with the common market, mainly due to the low
combined market shares in the Greek market for consumer finance
and the presence of a range of competitors, said the European
Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
