<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dasa, Lockheed Form Rocket Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Daimler Chrysler Aerospace (Dasa)
has formed a rocket joint venture with US company Lockheed Martin
in the latest shifting of the international aerospace industry
landscape, a Dasa spokesman said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"This is a sign that we also have very good connections with US
partners and are increasing such cooperation," the spokesman said,
noting the stronger German-American corporate rapport since the
merger which created the parent DaimlerChrysler company.
</P>
<P>
The new company, to be based in the town of Unterschleissheim,
near the south German city Munich, will be in charge of producing
specialized components, testing and logistics for the "Patriot"
PAC-3 anti-missile missile.
</P>
<P>
Dasa was rebuffed late last year in its efforts to merge with
British Aerospace, which instead chose to merge with GEC Marconi
to create Europe's largest defense weaponry corporation.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Dasa was continuing to keep its
European options open and that talks with potential partners were
continuing. On Thursday, Dasa chairman Manfred Bischoff met with
French government officials to discuss related business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
