<HEADLINE> East China Province To Develop Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province,
one of the nation's economic powerhouses, has decided to cooperate
with more overseas investors in developing its information
industry.
</P>
<P>
The province aims to turn the industry into a pillar of the
local economy and one of the strongest in the country in the near
future, said Wang Dechao, head of the provincial electronics
industry department.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, the province will give priority to the
development and production of mobile communications equipment,
computers, digital video disk players and digital TV sets.
</P>
<P>
A number of production centers are to be set up, focusing on
the manufacture of program-controlled switchboards, satellite
communications equipment and other high-tech electronic appliances.
</P>
<P>
Greater efforts will be made to develop the software industry,
and establish and improve dozens of applied information systems in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Jiangsu achieved a 24 percent growth in its
electronics industry and investors from the United States, Japan
and Taiwan region have operations there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
