</P>
<P>
-- The NASDAK composite index soared 96.06 points, or 4.16
percent to 2405.55, its biggest point move ever and its ninth best
in percentage terms. Federal Reserve Chairman Greenspan helped
spark the rally with positive comments on banking reform and
praise for the economy's strength.
</P>
<P>
-- Major U.S. steelmakers are in the final stages of preparing
a second round of unfair trade complaints against several
countries and could file them as early as next week, according to
people familiar with the plans. 
