<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cholera Breaks out in Northern Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- There are reports of serious
cholera breaking out in the famine-stricken border region of Gedo,
northern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest reports from the town of Bardera in
Gedo region, 14 people, mainly women and children, died of cholera
on Thursday alone, while 82 others were also hospitalized after
falling for the disease.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed Jama Ber, the governor of the region, said through the
VHF radio in the regional capital, Garbahaffey Town, that the
cholera disease is spreading in the community very fast, affecting
over 100 people per day. He characterized the situation as
desperate and alarming.
</P>
<P>
Local health authorities said severe diarrhea and dysentery are
also accompanying the cholera.  Ber said there's no single aid
agency fighting against the spread of the disease in the region
following what is called the temporary evacuation of the
international staff from the area in protest against the killing
of a Kenyan aid worker serving the Italian aid agency, Terra
Nuoya, in the region two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The local authorities also attributed the fast spread of the
disease to the water scarcity in the area especially in the remote
villages and the countryside. Reports said the situation has been
aggravated by the local movement of large number of families
displaced by famine and water shortage.
</P>
<P>
Ber said the current drought is the worst since 1974 when main
devastating Dabadher drought claimed the lives of thousands of
people
</P>
<P>
The authorities are complaining about the arrival of large
number of people coming from the regions of Bay, Bakol, Middle
Jubba and northeastern Kenya.  In Bulo Hawo Town of Gedo region
alone, over 500 refugees have crossed from the Kenyan border in
the past five days, said the district commissioner Haji Yussuf
Musa Abdi.
</P>
<P>
More than 8,000 families are now believed to be on the move in
search of food and water in Gedo region alone, while more than
4,000 other families are moving around in Bay region following the
prolonged drought and civil war that ravaged those regions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, over 700,000 people are believed to be suffering
from serious food shortage in southern Somalia following
insufficient rainfalls in the region in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The nomadic societies are equally suffering from the drought
after ban was imposed on Somalia's livestock exports to the Gulf
countries last year.
</P>
<P>
Over 80 percent of Somalia's population depend on the
livestock, especially the camels and goats, as the country's
largest exported item to the Arab countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990212.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Emphasizes Adherence To Multi-party Cooperation System (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said
today that China must adhere to the system of multi-party
cooperation and political consultation under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
There can be no ambiguity in this political principle and it
complies with China's actual conditions, Jiang told a forum for
non-Party personnel for the Spring Festival.
</P>
<P>
He extended new year's greetings to China's 8 non-Communist
parties, the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, and
people without party affiliation on behalf of the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council and praised their efforts in
political consultation, democratic supervision and participation
in political and government affairs over the past year.
</P>
<P>
He said that 1999 has special significance in China's
development because the country will celebrate its 50th birth
anniversary and resume exercise of sovereignty over Macao this
year.
</P>
<P>
The reforms are now at a critical period and people need to
work hard to settle problems in the economic and social life, he
said, reminding the audience that the effects of the Asian
financial crisis are still being felt in China, and economic
globalization is bringing both opportunities and challenges to
development.
</P>
<P>
"To realize the objectives of the reforms and construction, and
to maintain a stable society and sustainable economic growth, we
must continue to promote the political advantage of the patriotic
united front," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990212.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin On Multi-party Co-operation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said that China needs scientific analysis and to identify
risks and difficulties and its own advantages and strength and
asked non-Communist parties, the All-China Federation of Industry
and Commerce, and people everywhere to make a joint effort in the
socialist modernization cause.
</P>
<P>
Practice has shown that China's multi-party co-operation and
political consultation system under the leadership of the
Communist Party has its own advantages and vitality and provides
powerful political backing for reforms, development and stability,
he said.
</P>
<P>
This year will be the 50th anniversary of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference and the domestic and global
situation puts new demand on China's multi-party co-operation and
political consultation system, he said, and with the guidance of
Deng Xiaoping's concept of multi-party cooperation, China needs to
work hard to improve this system and to make full use of it in the
new circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the forum were Li Ruihuan and Hu Jintao and
leaders of the central committees of China's 8 non-Communist
parties, the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, and
some people without party affiliations.  
</P>
