<HEADLINE> EU Foreign Ministers to be Briefed on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 12 (Xinhua) - European Union foreign ministers
are to meet on Sunday for a briefing on the Kosovo peace talks
being held at Rambouillet outside Paris, Bonn Foreign Office
spokesman Martin Erdmann said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting would take place in Paris after a meeting of the
international Contact Group made up of the United States, Britain,
France, Germany, Italy and Russia on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The contact group is planning to take stock of the peace talks
and decide whether to extend them for another week or declare them
a failure.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said the
peace conference would be extended by another week.
</P>
<P>
After the Contact Group meeting, German Foreign Joschka Fischer,
who is also EU president, will brief those of his EU counterparts
whose countries are not members of the contact group.
</P>
<P>
Erdmann stressed that this EU meeting was not being called to
put pressure on the Serbs and Kosovo Albanians. Instead, it will
take stock and discuss a possible strategy for a final week of
talks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile NATO ambassadors met in Brussels Friday morning to
discuss strengthening NATO forces in Macedonia in preparation for
a mission in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The current force of 2,300 troops could be boosted to about 10,
000 to enable it to enforce an interim peace agreement. If the
Rambouillet talks were to fail, however, such a force would not be
needed, as NATO in that case is threatening to use air strikes
only. 
</P>
</TEXT>
