<HEADLINE> S.Korea Unveils Defense Programs for Next Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 12 (Xinhua) -- South Korea will invest some 26.
7 trillion won (21.36 billion U.S. dollars) over the next five
years in an ambitious weapons buying program, the Defense Ministry
announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The programs are composed of the destroyer-building project
code-named KDX-III, the next-generation fighter program, purchases
of attack helicopters, surface-to-air missiles and unmanned aerial
vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The weapons procurement program is part of the 81.5 trillion
won (67.15 billion dollars) defense expenditure plan to be
implemented over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The defense budget for the year 2000 will be 14.5 trillion won
(11.95 billion dollars), up from this year's 13.7 trillion won (11.
3 billion dollars), a spokesman for the Defense Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said it will cost more than 2.1 trillion won (1.
73 billion dollars) to acquire anti-tank attack helicopters such
as Apache or Tiger.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean army now has less advanced Cobra attack
helicopters, and the new program will upgrade the Army's anti-tank
attack capability.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean Navy will have three Aegis-class destroyers
within 10 years under a medium-term defense procurement project.
</P>
<P>
As for the next-generation fighter program, the ministry said
it was planning to buy some 60 new fighters.
</P>
<P>
Among its choices are Rafale of France, Eurofighter produced by
a European consortium, F-15 of the United States and Russia's
Sukhoi-35.
</P>
<P>
By early next year when the South Korea Fighter Program
finishes, the air force will acquire 120 F-16 Fighting Falcon jet
fighters. Twelve of the F-16s were manufactured by U.S. Lockheed
Martin, and the rest were assembled or produced by Samsung.
</P>
<P>
A program code-named SAM-X is related to the purchase either of
U.S.-made Patriot missiles or Russia's S-300 air defense system.
Under another program, an undisclosed number of unmanned
surveillance aircraft worth 100 billion won (82.4 million dollars)
will be bought in 2001 to 2002. The South Korean army already has
Israeli-made unmanned surveillance vehicles.
</P>
<P>
A program to build new submarines, code-named SSU, will start
in October this year, said the ministry spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
