<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Population Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG,February 12 (Xinhua) -- The estimated population of
Hong Kong at the end of 1998 was 6,805,600, according to figures
released Friday by the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
There was an increase of 188,500 persons, or a growth rate of 2.
8 percent, as compared with the figure at the end of 1997, said
the department.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, there were 53,100 births and 32,200
deaths in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The natural increase thus amounted to 20,900, accounting for 11
percent of the population growth. 
</P>
