<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Smaller Firms Expected to Boost Economic Growth (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ninety-nine percent of the officially registered industrial
enterprises in Anhui are small and medium-sized ones, and they
provide 77.3 percent of all jobs in the province, accounting for
60.2 percent of total salaries there, according to Wang Jinyuan,
deputy chief of the Enterprise Section of the Anhui Provincial
Commission for Economic Restructuring.
</P>
<P>
Nationwide, there are more than 10 million small and medium-
sized businesses in China, about 98.5 percent of all the nation's
enterprises. These enterprises account for 60 percent of the
national industrial output value, and 50 percent of all taxes and
profits. They also provide 70 percent of all jobs in the urban
areas.
</P>
<P>
Mao Yushi, director of the Unirule Institute of Economics in
Beijing, said that small and medium-sized businesses are in a
better position to take advantage of China's low labor costs than
large enterprises, which are often capital intensive.
</P>
<P>
"The small and medium-sized firms are the main locomotive to
activate economic growth at present, as well as a major source of
employment," Mao told Xinhua recently.
</P>
<P>
In recognition of the role played by small and medium-sized
firms in the national economy, Chinese authorities have unveiled a
series of supportive measures in recent years. The State Economic
and Trade Commission last year set up a new department responsible
for drafting policies to aid and steer the growth of these
businesses. And earlier this month, the government announced that
China is establishing a credit guarantee system to help them solve
financing difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Observers say that small and medium-sized businesses will play
an important role in ensuring the sustainable, rapid and healthy
growth of the Chinese economy when the overall performance of
large state-owned firms now has proved to be far from satisfactory,
and the economic environment remains uncertain both at home and
abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
