<HEADLINE> International Workshop on Oil Crops Ends in Maputo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A three-day International
Symposium on Sunflower and Other Oilseed Crops in Developing
Countries ended in Maputo Thursday, calling on world countries to
pay more attention to the production and study of the oil-bearing
crops.
</P>
<P>
The participants to the workshop urged the governments of the
developing countries to take measures to encourage the production
of and study on sunflower seeds and other oilseed crops so as to
meet the increasing demands for vegetarian oils.
</P>
<P>
They maintained that the seeds breeding project should be
worked out with the participation of the farmers and that much
importance should be put on the improvement and diversification of
the seeds and on the unit output of seeds and oil.
</P>
<P>
President of the Eduardo Mondiane University of Mozambique,
Brazao Mazula said at the closing session the workshop gave more
knowledge to people about oil crops and the development strategy
for oilseed crops, Mozambiques' Noticias newspaper reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Also at the event, some 100 experts and industrialists from
countries as China, India, Kenya, Zimbabwe, Zambia, Portugal and
France exchanged their views on the problems in the oilseed
production and oil processing in the developing world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
