<HEADLINE> Seoul Share Prices Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The share prices at the Seoul
Stock Market rose 5.3 percent Friday due to futures-linked buying.
</P>
<P>
The Korea Stock Price Index (KOSPI) jumped 27.78 points to
close at 551.77, returning to the 550-point level after one week.
</P>
<P>
A total of 153.9 million shares worth 1.3 trillion won (1.1
billion U.S. dollars) were traded. Winners outnumbered losers at
685 against 131 while 54 stocks remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Stock observers said an upswing in March futures contracts
prices sparked the futures-related buying by foreign investors,
who purchased 27.0 billion won.
</P>
<P>
Gains were across the board with electronics, machinery,
construction, banking, securities, and insurance sector stocks
rising in a technical rebound following days of heavy losses.
</P>
<P>
Shares of Hyundai Motor climbed 550 won despite reports that
the company recorded a net loss of 33.1 billion won last year.
</P>
<P>
Samsung Electronics stocks surged 5,200 won on news that the
company had successfully lowered its debt-to-equity ratio to below
the IMF-recommended 200 percent level due to its restructuring
efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
