<HEADLINE> China Revokes Five Trade Companies' Licenses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) has decided to revoke the
import licenses of 5 companies in Qinghai Province that have
defrauded people out of large amounts of foreign currency.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC said today that the decision is part of the nation's
effort to crack down on fraud in foreign exchange and was intended
to punish trade companies that have made illegal payments in
foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghai Provincial Electric Equipment and Machinery Import
and Export Company; Qinghai Provincial Cereals, Oils, and
Foodstuffs Import and Export Company; Qinghai Provincial Native
Products Import and Export Company; Qinghai Branch of the China
National Packaging Import and Export Corporation; and the Qinghai
Machinery Import and Export Corporation were found by the State
Administration of Exchange Control to have got 222.5 million U.S.
dollars worth of foreign exchange fraudulently, and to have "
severely affected the nation's normal order of finance and foreign
trade and economic co-operation."
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC has asked foreign trade and economic cooperation
departments at all levels to tighten foreign exchange settlement
controls for smoother growth in foreign trade and economic co-
operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
