<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 24.09 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Friday gained 24.09 points to
3,337.49 as against Thursday's close of 3,313.40.
</P>
<P>
The national index also gained by 10.44 points to 1,468.12 as
against the previous close of 1,457.68.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted marginally up at
339.60 and 133.16 from the last close of 336.77 and 132.05
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Pharmaceutical and software scrips once again stole the
limelight on the last day of the current settlement on the BSE
market Friday following fresh purchases by foreign institutional
investors and buying support from domestic operators. 
</P>
