<HEADLINE> Industrial, Commercial Bank Of China Providing 100 Billion Yuan in Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China will provide over 100 billion yuan (12 billion U.S.
dollars) in loans this year to support national economic
development, bank officials announced today.
</P>
<P>
The loans will focus on projects of highways,
telecommunications, water, gas, and power supplies, and cultural
facilities, with high-tech areas with great potential also being
given priority.
</P>
<P>
It will reduce funding this year for industries with backward
technology, low quality, or which waste resources and pollute the
environment.
</P>
<P>
The bank also plans to improve controls on how loans are used.
</P>
</TEXT>
