<HEADLINE> Macao Hotel Room Occupancy Rate Remains Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The hotel room occupancy rate in
Macao remained fairly low over the past year, latest official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
on Friday indicate that the average hotel room occupancy rate was
recorded at 53.1 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,156,071 people checked in Macao hotels in 1998,
down 2.4 percent from 1997. In particular, the number of people
living in three-star hotels dropped considerably.
</P>
<P>
There were 8,320 rooms available for passengers by the end of
last year in Macao, down 0.1 percent from a year earlier. Last
December, occupancy rate was 54.7 percent, and passengers spent 1.
39 nights on average in the hotels.
</P>
<P>
The leading markets for Macao hotels are Hong Kong, China's
mainland and Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
