<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Up 3.05 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices
surged 3.05 percent in futures-driven buying on Friday following
strong overnight gains on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index gained 278.62 points to end at 9,425.42
while turnover amounted to 3.119 billion HK dollars (340 million U.
S. dollars), 744 million HK dollars (95 million U.S. dollars) more
than that of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The share prices were up 113.35 points, or 1.24 percent, to 9,
260.15 after the market was opened. It added 156.22 points to
close the mid-session at 9,303.02.
</P>
<P>
Sectors of finance, utilities, properties, and commerce and
industry registered respective gains of 3.17 percent, 1.76 percent,
3.71 percent and 3.80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The red-chip Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporation Index added
3.7 percent while H-share index rose 2.58 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first day of the week's trading, the Hang Seng Index
shed 50.6 points to end at 9,139.6. It rose 1.14 percent to finish
at 9,244.49 on the following day.
</P>
<P>
A fall on Wall Street pulled Hong Kong shares down 1.82 percent
on Wednesday and the Hang Seng Index edged up slightly on Thursday
to 9,146.8 points.
</P>
<P>
The five trading days all saw turnover below 3.15 billion HK
dollars (404 million U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
