<HEADLINE> Fire Hits Residential House in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A fire Friday destroyed a
two-story residential house in southern Manila, damaging an
estimated 20,000 U.S. dollars worth of property.
</P>
<P>
Nobody was injured in the fire, the Bureau of Fire Protection's
National Capital Regional Office said.
</P>
<P>
The fire started from a vacant room on the second floor of the
house at 8:25 in the morning and was put out half an hour later,
fire officials said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire was still unknown, they said. 
</P>
