<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Friday but were off their
highs ahead of a long festive break until next Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The market will be closed for three days from Monday for
Chinese New Year.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index, which
touched an intra-day high of 575.19, gained 7.84 points to 570.79,
the all-share Emas index surged 2.33 points to 145.07, the
Industrial index added 5.27 points to 1,039.64 and the Second
Board index was up 4.09 points to 153.52.
</P>
<P>
Advancers thumped decliners by 582 to 74 while 90 counters were
unchanged, 163 untraded and 18 others suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 205.37 million shares worth
459.38 million ringgit (about 120.889 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 144.309 million shares at 327.774 million ringgit
(about 86.256 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
