<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian President Calls for More Concerns About </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Indian President K. R.
Narayanan Friday called upon the whole country to make all efforts
to put an end to indifference towards the disabled.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating a new training center for the mentally handicapped
in Calcutta, 1,461 km southeast of New Delhi, Narayanan said that
it was the moral obligation of society to pay more attention to
the handicapped people in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Traditionally our society is not oozing with sympathy for the
mentally and physically handicapped. We have to overcome this
attitude," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
India has about 90 million disabled and 24 million of them are
mentally handicapped.
</P>
<P>
The Union government had enacted a law in 1995 ensuring equal
opportunity for the disabled and their participation in the
national life.
</P>
<P>
This law must make a fact of life, the president said, adding
that it was necessary to mobilize the resources of the society and
develop scientific programs to help them conquer their
disabilities and become full participants in the life of the
nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
