<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Returns Home From China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister
Hun Sen returned home Friday from China, ending his four-day
official visit at the invitation of his Chinese counterpart Zhu
Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Meeting him and his party at the Pochentong Airport were Deputy
Prime Ministers Sar Kheng and Tol Lah and other government
officials as well as Chinese charge d'affairs ad interim Zhang
Jinfeng.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Hor Nam Hong told reporters that the four-day
China visit was "very successful" and the two sides inked five
agreements.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in China, Hun Sen met with Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference Li Ruihuan. Hun Sen
also held talks with Prime Minister Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen began his China visit on February 9, accompanied by
Foreign Minister Hor Nam Hong, Minister of the Council of
Ministers Sok An and Finance Minister Keat Chhon and some other
government officials.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen and his party left Beijing on February 11 for Kunming,
capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, to continue their
China visit.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen was last in Beijing in December last year when he
visited King Sihanouk, who was undergoing medical treatment there.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
