<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slide on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices gyrated from
positive to negative territory on the Singapore Stock Market
Friday, dragged down by profit-taking ahead of the Lunar New Year
celebration next week.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) slid down 2.32 points
to end at 1354.85 points in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume contracted to 126.82 million units valued at
229.85 million Singapore dollars (about 135.89 million U.S.
dollars). Losers outnumbered gainers by 123 to 80 while 221
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 12.68 million share parcel by the
KepTLDBS w00 that was transacted at 0.525 Singapore dollars per
share. DBS Land was the second most heavily traded stock with a
turnover of 9.34 million shares. CK Tang w99 was next with 8.24
million units done.
</P>
<P>
SPH was the biggest gainer of the day with a run-up of 60 cents
to 18.10 Singapore dollars. It was followed by SPH that gained 40
cents to finish at 18.10 Singapore dollars. DBS F and UOB F went
up 30 cents to end at 12.00 and 9.15 Singapore dollars
respectively. Elec &AMP; E also edged up 30 cents but closed at 5.75
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, C &AMP; C headed the descent of the day with a
loss of 40 cents to 6.40 Singapore dollars. DBS sank 35 cents to
end at 8.15 Singapore dollars. OCBC retreated 25 cents to end at
7.65 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said shares were broadly lower following a technical
surge on Thursday although blue chips managed slight gains at
midday.
</P>
<P>
They noted that an overnight rally on Wall Street helped to
support the market sentiment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
