<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Heads Upward This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus stock market
skyrocketed for the fifth consecutive day holding onto its
unprecedented momentum, a weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), said banking stocks were trading
this week in a frenzy, absorbing about 70 percent of the weekly
volume of transactions.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index moved into uncharted territory,
breaking through the 600 level. It closed on February 11 at
622.2 points, registering on a fifth consecutive day an all-time
high record.
</P>
<P>
The gains of 5.2 percent (30.5 points) on Thursday were
the highest daily gains ever achieved in the market's history.
The weekly gains are 16.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index (having a base year of 100 on
December 1983 surpassed, on the February 2, for the first time
after 3 years, its previous all-time high record of 522 points
held since February 1996.
</P>
<P>
It is to be noted that it moved from the 500 level to
the 600 level within 14 trading days, covering 122 points. The
market's capital appreciation is 37 percent so far in the
current year.
</P>
<P>
Total volume of transactions for the last five trading
days, reached 42.3 million Cyprus pounds (84.6 million U.S.
dollars) and since the beginning of the year 144.5 million
pounds (289.0 million dollars). This volume of the first seven
weeks of the year is about 42 percent of that registered for
the whole of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
