<DOCNO> XIE19990212.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand's Population Exceeds 3.8 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The resident population of
New
Zealand was estimated at 3,803,900 at the end of 1998, an increase
of
22,600 or 0.6 percent over the 1997 figure, Statistics New Zealand
said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 0.6 growth rate is less than half the 1.4 percent average
annual
growth rate for the previous five years.
</P>
<P>
In a media release, Statistics NZ noted that a significant
turnaround
in the external migration balance has been the main factor in the
slower
growth.
</P>
<P>
Permanent and long-term departures exceeded arrivals by 6,300
last
year, compared with a net migration gain of 7,600 in 1997. The
natural
increase (excess of births over deaths) fell from 30,300 in 1997
to
28,900 in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Population aging is continuing in New Zealand. The median age
of the
New Zealand population has increased by 2.3 years since 1991. Half
the
population is now over the age of 33.9 years, compared with 32.6
years
in 1994 and 31.6 years in 1991, according to the media release.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
