<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Steve Smith scored 11 of
his 17 points during a masterful first quarter by the Atlanta
Hawks with a 100-88 victory over the Charlotte Hornets.
</P>
<P>
Smith made 4-of-5 shots in the opening period and went on to
lead the team in scoring for the fifth time in as many games,
helping Atlanta to a 3-0 home record and a 4-1 mark overall.
</P>
<P>
Alan Henderson and LaPhonso Ellis added 16 points apiece and
Dikembe Mutombo grabbed 18 rebounds for the Hawks, who last season
lost to the Hornets in the opening round of the playoffs after
winning all four regular-season meeting.
</P>
