<HEADLINE> Slovenia Hopes to Strengthen Cooperation with Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Slovenian Prime
Minister Janez Drnovsek said Slovenia hoped to strengthen
cooperation with Poland in the economic area and ease integration
with the European Union.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement during a meeting with his Polish
counterpart Jerzy Buzek and presidents of the parliament and the
senate, the Polish news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Slovenian premier said he also hoped Poland would support
his country's efforts to join the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
He said it was necessary for the two countries to strengthen
cooperation to ensure a speedy integration with the EU since the
two were among the first group of countries permitted to enter.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that both the Polish parliament president and
senate president had expressed support for Slovenia's bid for NATO
membership.
</P>
<P>
Poland will become a NATO member on March 12.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers also discussed bilateral trade, which
stood at 213 million U.S. dollars in the recent two months.
</P>
<P>
Drnovsek arrived here on Wednesday for a two-day official visit
to Poland, his first visit to the country. 
</P>
