<HEADLINE> 47 Indian Industries Register Lower Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- 47 Indian industries had
registered lower growth rate in the first nine months of the
current fiscal year 1998-99 (April 1, 1998-March 31, 1999),
official sources said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Interestingly, the figures-calculated on the basis of
information provided by Associations Council of the Confederation
of Indian Industry (CII) members and 77 affiliated bodies, which
account for over 65 percent of the total output in most cases, do
not support the official stance: an industrial revival is in the
offing.
</P>
<P>
The trend worsened gradually during the period under review.
The April-September figures showed 39 sectors in the positive,
while the number came down to 37 in April-October. In
April-December, 47 sectors posted lower growth rate against the
corresponding period of 1997 and only 29 showed improvement and
four remained stagnant, CII sources said.
</P>
<P>
Among consumer durables, refrigerators registered a decline of
11-15 percent, air-conditioners 13-20 percent and washing machines
10-20 percent. Color television, which had been one of the star
performers in recent times, registered a decline of 20-22 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among other crucial sectors, there was continued decline in
cement (4.5-9.5 percent), steel (-0.6- -2.2 percent), machine
tools (-8.9- -27 percent) polyester filament yarn (17-26 percent),
etc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
