<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Host Fourth International Heroin Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Fourth International Heroin
Conference will be held here from February 23 to 26, according to
an official announcement Friday.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's hosting of the four-day conference was offered by the
 Office of Director-General of Interpol (ODGI) which proposed
Myanmar as the venue of the conference in view of Myanmar's
realization of the objectives of the ODGI and making the country's
significant anti-narcotics activities known to the world.
</P>
<P>
Several dozens of countries are expected to attend the
conference.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the United States, Britain and some other European
countries have announced boycott of the conference.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the refusal of the United States and Britain to
participate in the conference, the Myanmar government has
expressed great regret over their move.
</P>
<P>
The Office of the Strategic Studies of the Myanmar Ministry of
Defense said in a statement issued here Wednesday that "the
international drug trade is an urgent problem which needs to be
addressed in a spirit of mutual cooperation by the entire world
community."
</P>
<P>
The statement urged the two countries to put politics aside for
the sake of the millions of people around the world whose lives
are threatened by the drug trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
