<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Migrant Workers Remit Rs. 60 Billion in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan migrant workers in
the Middle East and Far East have remitted 60 billion rupees (880
million U.S. dollars) in 1998, a nine percent increase in rupee
terms over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Sixty percent of this remittance was sent in to the country by
house maids, according to the Foreign Employment Bureau (FEB).
</P>
<P>
There are around one million Sri Lankan migrant workers in
these regions. So far 158,286 persons have registered with the
FEB, of whom 65 percent were females.
</P>
<P>
Migrant workers who register with the FEB are guaranteed
special protection under a contract.
</P>
<P>
According to FEB statistics there has been a six percent rise
in the number of migrant workers despite the East Asian financial
crisis and the drop in oil prices in the Middle East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
