<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 38,000 Accidents and Catastrophes Reported in Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- A total of 38,000 accidents
and natural catastrophes occurred in Kazakhstan in 1998, causing
casualties to 29,000 people and material losses estimated at 4.9
billion tenge (about 570 million U.S. dollars), a senior official
announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A chief of Kazakhstan emergency information bureau said the
number of accidents and incidents decreased by 9.2 percent
compared to the year 1997.
</P>
<P>
About 16,000 persons were killed or injured in traffic
accidents in 1998, an increase of 3.7 percent over 1997.
</P>
<P>
About 20,000 fires broke out in 1998 and caused losses worth 2.
8 billion tenge ( about 320 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Incidents caused by avalanches, hurricanes and floods totaled
160, an increase of 26.5 percent compared to 1997.
</P>
<P>
He warned local officials to take preventive measures to avert
future accidents and limit potential damage and death during
natural catastrophes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
