<DOCNO> XIE19990212.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Set Up National Railway Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka is soon to establish
a national railway museum to exhibit monuments of the Railway
Department during its 135-year history, the official Daily News
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The museum is to be set up at a 75-year-old building complex at
Ratmalana, southern suburb of the capital Colombo, which formerly
served as the Railway Officers Welfare Club, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The National Railway Museum Steering Committee (NRMSC) expects
to complete the museum stage by stage and to open it for the
public within this year.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits will include steam locomotives, diesel engines,
old coaches and an assortment of railway articles such as
whistles, uniforms and lanterns, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The NRMSC hopes to start joint programs with the Department of
Education and the Ministry of Tourism to attract school children,
students and tourists as the museum will be an effective medium of
education and interactive entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Funds needed to restore the museum exhibits will be raised from
the private sector while some items have already been restored by
apprentices of the German Technical Training Institute at
Ratmalana.
</P>
<P>
The museum will also have an auditorium and audio visual aides,
a library, a landscaped garden and working scale models in a
scenic setting.
</P>
<P>
Simulations on computer screens of signals and railways
enabling a hand-on demonstration of the railway system will also
be part of the museum, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
