<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Woman of 119-year-old Inquired by Guinness Book of Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 11 (Xinhua) - The London headquarters of the
Guinness Book of Records has sent another letter to Bulgarian
centenarian Faime Hassanova, who is 119 years old, asking for more
information about the nominated oldest person on Earth.
</P>
<P>
Biography of Granny Faime and more information about her late
husband are required by Guinness.
</P>
<P>
An initiative committee, chaired by Mayor Valentin Gadjev of
Madan, a south central Bulgarian town where Granny Faime lives,
submitted her bid for entry in the Guinness Book of Records last
year.
</P>
<P>
The London headquarters has accepted the nomination and is now
verifying the documentary evidence of the woman's age.
</P>
<P>
The municipal officials told Guinness that Granny Faime's
husband Mehmed Hassanov died at the age of 108, and Faime was
married at the age of 12 to Mehmed, who was then 35.
</P>
<P>
The municipal administration also enclosed a family tree of the
oldest Bulgarian, listing her five children, 16 grandchildren, 17
great grandchildren and three great great grandchildren. She
survives three of her children.
</P>
<P>
The municipal administration is preparing for celebration of
Granny Faime's 120th birthday on April 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
