<DOCNO> XIE19990212.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Attracts Postgraduate Candidates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial city, has attracted a record 31,200
postgraduate candidates, from throughout the nation this year.
</P>
<P>
The candidates, which represent 10 percent of the nationwide
total, participated in the national entrance examinations held
between January 30 and February 1.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 17 percent of the individuals have applied
to study business administration. Other areas drawing large
numbers of candidates include finance, enterprise management and
computer technology.
</P>
<P>
A small number of candidates have exhibited interest in
specialties such as economic history, as well as nuclear,
molecular and plasma physics.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Shanghai Municipal Education Commission
said the trend is in line with the city's increasing demands for
professionals in areas such as new and high technology, business
administration, finance and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has focused on developing a knowledge-based economy in
recent years and has achieved major progress in establishing
itself as an international center for shipping, finance and
information technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
