<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close 4.2 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Mexican stocks closed more
than 4 percent higher than the previous day on gains in the U.S.
and Latin American markets Thursday, fueling confidence in the
Mexican economy.
</P>
<P>
The key IPC index rose 166.25 points, or 4.22 percent, to 4,107.
74 points, closing above 4,100 points for the first time since
November 11. At the end of 1998, the IPC stood at 3,959.66 points.
</P>
<P>
Volume was fairly high at 142.2 million U.S. dollars on 96.6
million shares traded, compared to Wednesday's 115 million dollars
on 66.4 million shares traded.
</P>
<P>
Mexican stocks closed the day higher following the rally of U.S.
stocks and a 2 percent rise of the U.S. Dow Jones Industrial
Average Index.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-five out of 89 issues traded went up while 14 dropped and
10 remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Analysts and traders said significant fourth-quarter earnings
on the domestic market and a stronger currency rate also prompted
the stocks' rally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
