<HEADLINE> Regional Bank Postpones Loan to Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) has postponed to next year a 150 million-U.
S.-dollar loan to Costa Rica, IDB representative Bertus Meins said
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Meins said the IDB has exhausted its quick-loan funds since
most of the money had been granted to Central American countries
devastated by Hurricane Mitch.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica central bank President Eduardo Lizano said that they
could float 300 million dollars worth of bonds on international
markets to raise funds.
</P>
<P>
The IDB has already earmarked 120 million dollars of loans for
Costa Rica's reform and the scheduled privatization program.
</P>
<P>
Meins said Costa Rica should improve its port, airport and
highway infrastructure to attract more foreign investments.
</P>
</TEXT>
