<HEADLINE> Rural Income Growth Outstrips Urban Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The growth rate for rural income was 11.8 percent greater than
the level for urban residents.
</P>
<P>
A provincial agricultural official attributed the rise in rural
incomes to increased inputs to agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the local government allocated 1.5 billion
yuan to the agricultural sector during 1998, with government loans
to the sector surpassing the 1997 figure by some two billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Other factors contributing to rising rural income levels
included favorable weather conditions, structural readjustments
and the development of processing industries, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning's grain output for the year hit a record 18 billion kg,
with considerable increases in output also recorded for meat,
vegetables and aquatic products.  
</P>
