<HEADLINE> 50 Brazilians Missing in Shipwreck </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- About 50 Brazilians were
reported missing on Thursday after a shipwreck Wednesday night on
the Madeira river in the state of Amazonas.
</P>
<P>
The ship Ana Maria VIII, with 150 passengers on board, was
sailing from the town of Porto Velho to the port of Manaus.
</P>
<P>
Survivors said about 100 victims were rescued by another ship
sailing down the river at the time of the accident.
</P>
<P>
The Manaus firefighters corps said Thursday that rescuers
continued their search but the Maderia's murky waters impeded them
from locating those missing.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still officially unknown, but
rescuers have attributed it to overload of passengers. The ship's
safety certificate expired in may 1998.  
</P>
