<HEADLINE> Security Council Renews U.N. Mission in Western Sahara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security
Council Thursday unanimously decided to extend the mandate of the
United Nations Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara
(MINURSO) until March 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The decision, contained in a resolution adopted by the 15
Security Council members, was "to allow for consultations in the
hope and expectation of agreement on the protocols on
identification, appeals and repatriation planning activities, as
well as on the essential issue of the implementation calendar."
</P>
<P>
The Security Council asked both parties to take concrete action
to enable the office of the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees to carry out the necessary preparatory work for the
repatriation of Saharan refugees eligible to vote, and their
immediate families, the resolution said.
</P>
<P>
The repatriation will be done under the Settlement Plan, the
resolution said. 
</P>
