<HEADLINE> U.N. to Unveil Three Panels on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The composition of
three panels to review key aspects of U.N. relations with Iraq may
be announced late Friday and they could begin to work a week or so
later, their Chairman Celso Amorim said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the press, Celso Amorim, Brazil's ambassador to the
United Nations, said, "I hope I will be able to finalize the
panels today or tomorrow, to make an announcement by tomorrow
evening probably."
</P>
<P>
