<HEADLINE> IDB Launches 1 Billion Dollar Global Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank launched Thursday its second 1 billion U.S.
dollar global bond issue of the current calendar year, paying a
semiannual coupon of 5.125 percent.
</P>
<P>
Goldman Sachs and Warburg Dillon Read are the joint lead
managers of the two-year issue, which matures on February 22, 2001
and has a re-offer price of 99.946 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that investor response to the issue was
favorable, with 40 percent of the bond issue sold in the Americas,
35 percent in Europe and the Middle East, and 25 percent in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue will be used to help finance the
social and economic development of the IDB's Latin American and
Caribbean member countries. 
</P>
